author: wn.com
title: Liberal party divided over gay marriage proposal
text: Entrenched divisions between conservatives and moderates within the new Turnbull Government have flared again. Conservatives in the Coalition have responded angrily to a proposal from Liberal MP and same sex marriage campaigner, Warren Entsch, to have a vote in the Parliament on marriage equality before the next election. The legislation would then only come into effect if a popular vote was carried after the election. ...
